- 'High-priority flowers' refer to applications with a priority class of 'High';
- 'Blooming' refers to applications with a status of 'Active';
- 'Visited by more than one bee' refers to applications that have experienced more than one alert.

- An application's `priority_class` determines its priority level within the same environment;
- `priority_rank` of 1 indicates the highest priority;
- `prev_priority` being NULL means there is no other application with a higher priority in the same environment.

- Active applications are those with a status of 'Active';
- Average CPU usage and average memory usage are metrics that indicate the typical resource consumption of an application;
- Maximum response time is the longest time taken for an application to respond to a request;
- Critical and warning alerts are notifications that indicate the severity of issues affecting the application's performance.

sql:
SELECT app_id, AVG(cpu_usage) AS avg_cpu_usage, AVG(memory_usage) AS avg_memory_usage, AVG(disk_usage) AS avg_disk_usage
FROM application_metrics
GROUP BY app_id;

